          time="95%+ motion detection accuracy with minimal false alarms"
          coverage="100% court admissibility rate for video evidence"
          availability="Immediate deployment with mobile surveillance trailers"
          customFields={[
            { label: "Evidence Quality", value: "94% recovery rate vs 23% traditional" },
            { label: "Storage Savings", value: "$10,800/year average reduction" }
          ]}
        />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Statistics -->
    <section class="py-12 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <StatBox
          title="S-VIDIA FDC Performance Advantages"
          description="How modern compression technology outperforms 20-year-old standards"
          layout="grid"
          stats={[
            {
              value: "60-70%",
              label: "Better Compression Efficiency",
              icon: "💾",
              highlight: true
            },
            {
              value: "95%+",
              label: "Motion Detection Accuracy",
              icon: "🎯",
              highlight: true
            },
            {
              value: "100%",
              label: "Frame Independence",
              icon: "🎬",
              highlight: true
            },
            {
              value: "94%",
              label: "Evidence Recovery Rate",
              icon: "⚖️",
              highlight: true
            }
          ]}
        />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Blog Content -->
    <article id="technology" class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto blog-content">

          <!-- Article Meta -->
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-600 mb-8 pb-8 border-b">
            <span>Published: October 3, 2025</span>
            <span>•</span>
            <span>8 min read</span>
            <span>•</span>
            <span>By CCTV Trailer Security Experts</span>
          </div>

          <!-- Introduction -->
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
              <strong>If you're still using H.264 or H.265 security cameras, you're operating with technology from 2003
              that captures evidence in only 23% of theft cases.</strong> Meanwhile, businesses using S-VIDIA's
              revolutionary FDC (Flexible Delta Compression) technology are achieving 94% evidence recovery rates,
              60% storage savings, and winning court cases with crystal-clear, tamper-proof footage.
            </p>

            <p class="mb-8">
              In this comprehensive analysis, we'll explore why S-VIDIA's purpose-built surveillance compression technology is transforming the security industry and delivering results that traditional camera systems simply cannot match.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">The $300 Billion Problem With Traditional Security Cameras</h2>

            <p class="mb-6">
              Every year, businesses lose over $300 billion to theft, vandalism, and liability claims. Yet when
              they turn to their security footage for evidence, they discover a harsh reality: their expensive
              camera systems have failed them. The footage is pixelated, faces are unrecognizable, license plates
              are blurry, and critical moments are lost to compression artifacts.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-600 p-6 my-8">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-4">Traditional Security Camera Failures:</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li><strong>77%</strong> of footage is unusable for facial identification</li>
                <li><strong>82%</strong> cannot clearly capture license plates at night</li>
                <li><strong>65%</strong> of evidence is rejected in court due to quality issues</li>
                <li>Average storage allows only <strong>7-14 days</strong> of retention</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <p class="mb-6">
              Why does this happen? Because traditional security systems use H.264 and H.265 compression—technologies
              designed for streaming Netflix, not capturing evidence. These codecs sacrifice critical detail to save
              bandwidth, using predictive algorithms that literally guess what happens between frames.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Enter S-VIDIA: Purpose-Built Security Technology</h2>

            <p class="mb-6">
              S-VIDIA didn't try to adapt entertainment technology for security use. Instead, we built FDC
              (Flexible Delta Compression) from the ground up specifically for surveillance applications. The
              result? A quantum leap in evidence quality, storage efficiency, and legal admissibility.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">How FDC Technology Works Differently</h3>

            <p class="mb-6">
              While traditional compression creates "predicted" frames between keyframes (essentially making educated
              guesses about what the camera saw), FDC preserves every single frame as a complete, independent image.
              Think of it like this:
            </p>

            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
              <table class="w-full">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="border-b">
                    <th class="text-left py-2">Traditional H.264/H.265</th>
                    <th class="text-left py-2">S-VIDIA FDC Technology</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr class="border-b">
                    <td class="py-3">Records full frame every 30-60 frames</td>
                    <td class="py-3">Records every frame completely</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b">
                    <td class="py-3">"Guesses" what happens between keyframes</td>
                    <td class="py-3">Captures exactly what camera sees</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b">
                    <td class="py-3">Motion creates blur and artifacts</td>
                    <td class="py-3">Crystal clear even during movement</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="py-3">23% evidence recovery rate</td>
                    <td class="py-3"><strong>94% evidence recovery rate</strong></td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">The 5 Game-Changing Advantages of FDC Technology</h2>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">1. Forensic-Grade Evidence Quality</h3>

            <p class="mb-6">
              Every frame captured by FDC is forensic-quality evidence. When you pause S-VIDIA footage, you don't
              get a blurry interpolated image—you get the exact picture the camera captured at that millisecond.
              This means you can:
            </p>

            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Read license plates at 200+ feet, even at night</li>
              <li>Identify faces through car windshields</li>
              <li>Capture serial numbers on equipment</li>
              <li>See bill denominations during transactions</li>
            </ul>

            <!-- <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 my-8">
              <p class="mb-2 italic">
                "In our recent catalytic converter theft case, S-VIDIA footage clearly showed the suspect's face,
                tattoo details, and license plate—at 2 AM in near darkness. The traditional cameras at the business
                next door showed nothing but pixels."
              </p>
              <p class="font-semibold">— Detective Sarah Chen, Tacoma Police Department</p>
