            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">2. Revolutionary Storage Efficiency</h3>

            <p class="mb-6">
              Despite recording higher quality footage, FDC actually uses 60% less storage than H.264. How? By
              using intelligent scene analysis to separate static backgrounds from moving objects. The system only
              records what changes, not what stays the same.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
              <h4 class="font-semibold mb-4">Storage Cost Comparison (30-Day Retention, 20 Cameras):</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Traditional H.264:</strong> 120TB required = $18,000/year</li>
                <li><strong>S-VIDIA FDC:</strong> 48TB required = $7,200/year</li>
                <li class="pt-2 border-t font-semibold text-green-700"><strong>Annual Savings:</strong> $10,800 (60% reduction)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">3. Legal Compliance & Court Admissibility</h3>

            <p class="mb-6">
              Unlike traditional compression that alters footage through prediction algorithms, every FDC frame is:
            </p>

            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Individually watermarked with cryptographic signatures</li>
              <li>AES-256 encrypted for tamper-proof chain of custody</li>
              <li>Time-synchronized with atomic clock precision</li>
              <li>Audit-logged for complete access history</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mb-6">
              This means S-VIDIA footage has never been rejected in court for authenticity concerns—a claim no
              H.264/H.265 system can make.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">4. Intelligent Motion Detection with 95% Accuracy</h3>

            <p class="mb-6">
              Traditional cameras generate hundreds of false alarms from shadows, weather, and animals. FDC's
              intelligent analytics achieve 95% accuracy by analyzing uncompressed video in real-time. The system
              distinguishes between:
            </p>

            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
              <li>People vs. shadows</li>
              <li>Vehicles vs. weather</li>
              <li>Threats vs. normal activity</li>
              <li>Authorized vs. unauthorized movement</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-600 p-6 my-8">
              <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Real-World Impact:</h4>
              <p>
                A Tacoma auto dealership reduced false alarms from 47 per day to just 2, saving their security
                team 8 hours daily while catching 3 actual theft attempts they would have missed.
              </p>
            </div>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">5. Lightning-Fast Evidence Retrieval</h3>

            <p class="mb-6">
              With traditional systems, finding a specific incident means watching hours of footage. FDC's
              motion-based indexing lets you search by:
            </p>

            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Specific areas of the frame</li>
              <li>Time ranges</li>
              <li>Motion patterns</li>
              <li>Object types (person, vehicle, etc.)</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mb-8">
              What used to take hours now takes seconds. Law enforcement can get the evidence they need immediately,
              increasing the chances of recovery and prosecution.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Real-World Applications Proving FDC Superiority</h2>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Auto Dealerships: From Blur to Crystal Clear</h3>

            <p class="mb-6">
